## Code Philosophy

- Clear naming over comments (comments = naming failure)
- Start simple, add complexity only when forced
- Prefer stdlib over external deps
- **Work → Right → Fast | Simple > Complex**

## Absolute Rules

### ZERO COMMENTS (Unless WHY)
```go
// ❌ NEVER: // Create a new user
// ✅ ACCEPTABLE: // Required by legacy API
```

### NO AI-STYLE CODE
```go
// ❌ applicationConfiguration := config.Load()
// ✅ cfg := config.Load()
```

## Layer Dependencies (Inward Only)

```
Transport → UseCase → Domain ← Repository ← Infrastructure
```

| Layer | Location | Rules |
|-------|----------|-------|
| Domain | `/internal/domain/` | ZERO external deps, NO struct tags |
| Repository | `/internal/repository/` | Private models, mappers |
| UseCase | `/internal/usecase/` | Business orchestration |
| Transport | `/internal/transport/` | Private DTOs, validation |

## Naming

- Variables: `cfg`, `repo`, `srv`, `pool`, `ctx`, `req`, `resp`, `err`
- Constructors: `New()` public, `new*()` private
- Structs: private by default
- Receivers: short (`s`, `u`, `r`)

## Error Handling

```go
// ✅ return fmt.Errorf("query user %s: %w", id, err)
// ❌ return fmt.Errorf("Failed to query: %w", err)
```

